v0.7.0: elevation split, DO_NOT_SHARE layout, cdb deep analysis, scope &
collector health reporting, UI-wide redaction, build-kind labels

Elevation split: unelevated parent spawns UAC helper only for minidump copy
(ElevatedDumpCopy). Staging path validated against %LOCALAPPDATA%\FLARE with
trailing-separator boundary, reparse-point re-check before each File.Copy,
and registry-sourced source path constrained under %SystemRoot%.

Storage layout: FlareStorage centralizes paths. Raw minidumps and cdb
transcripts live under DO_NOT_SHARE/; the user-visible Reports/ folder holds
only the generated .txt. Transient elevated-helper staging lives under
DO_NOT_SHARE/Staging/. One-shot migration from 0.6.x layouts on first run.

cdb integration: CdbLocator restricts resolution to Microsoft-managed
debugger roots (no PATH fallback, no user override). CdbRunner drives
!analyze -v with summary extraction. CdbAnalysisCache keys per-dump on
size+mtime+version, atomic write via temp+Replace, trailer sentinel rejects
crash-truncated bodies.

Redaction: ReportRedaction module scrubs UUID, computer name, and Windows
user paths (including %APPDATA%/%LOCALAPPDATA%/%TEMP%/%TMP%/OneDrive roots);
on by default. Applied to the report .txt, the visible run log, the bottom
status bar, the OUTPUT path row and tooltip, the cdb status tooltip, and
the unhandled-exception popup. UI-side egress goes through a single
MainViewModel.Display helper mirroring FlareRunner.RedactLogMessage; the
persistent surfaces re-render live when the toggle flips. Raw cdb
transcripts under DO_NOT_SHARE/ are not scrubbed.

Report scope & collector health: SCOPE block at the top of every report
discloses requested window, System/Application Event Log retention floors,
per-collector cap hits, and collector notices (canary/skipped/failure).
Multi-GPU SM-localization conclusions are suppressed when more than one
NVIDIA adapter is present. Concentration verdicts in ReportAnalysis pair
permissive heuristics with calibrated prose so weak signals read as
anecdotal rather than categorical.

Collectors: SystemInfo (board/BIOS/CPU/RAM). GpuInfo gains PCIe current/max
gen+width with LOWER AT SAMPLE annotation, BAR1/ReBAR detection, multi-GPU
detection. BugcheckCatalog covers MDMP, PAGEDUMP, PAGEDU64. Kernel-Power 41
bugcheck extraction. NVIDIA setupapi.dev.log parser. NvidiaDriverVersion
converts Windows 4-part to marketing form.

Format-drift canaries: setupapi (scheme mismatch), cdb (!analyze banner
without expected tags), nvlddmkm (events read but none classified). Each
canary surfaces in the SCOPE block of the saved report.

Robustness: regex match timeouts across event-log parsing, fatal.log with
1 MB rotation, corrupt settings.json quarantined to .corrupt, settings
writes debounced and atomic, cancellation threaded through every collector.

Build-kind label: FlareIsRelease MSBuild flag, set only on tag builds by
CI and build-exe.ps1, embeds an AssemblyMetadata attribute. BuildBanner
turns it plus the InformationalVersion into a title-bar prefix
([DEV BUILD] / [SNAPSHOT] / clean) and a single-line About entry
(release / snapshot (hash) / local dev build / non-release build) so the
running binary's provenance is unambiguous on screen.

UI: MainWindow.xaml drops the Output Path text input row (folder is fixed
to %LOCALAPPDATA%\FLARE\Reports). UseLayoutRounding and SnapsToDevicePixels
default true on every Window via the shared style so 1-DIP hairlines render
at full brush color regardless of DPI scale. AboutWindow gains hairline
edges matching MainWindow's pattern.

Structure: ReportInput record replaces 10-arg Generate. ReadEvents<T>
helper collapses EventLogReader loops with optional scan-cap. ReportAnalysis
owns the localization heuristic. FlareDependencies test seam lets the
pipeline run without live Windows APIs.

Application crash correlation distinguishes distinct crashes from pair
count. Report section numbering is dynamic (no gaps when optional sections
absent).

CI: SHA-pinned actions, SHA256SUMS.txt for zip and exe, packaged-binary
smoke tests (startup and helper refusal). Tag builds pass FlareIsRelease=true
through to the assembly. Release job now checks out the repo and uses
HISTORY.log as the GitHub Release body, replacing the prior
tag-annotation-as-body convention.

392 xUnit tests covering parsers, pipeline, redaction (incl. UI surface
pins), cache invalidation, trusted-root checks, helper refusal codes,
canaries, build-kind label format.

Docs: ARCHITECTURE.md, CONTRIBUTING.md, README updated for DO_NOT_SHARE
layout, redaction surface scope, build-kind labels, and the unsigned-binary
stance. README error-summary line dropped the obsolete "probability
calculations" claim in favor of "SM coordinate concentration analysis"
matching the calibrated-prose verdicts in ReportAnalysis. README dump-format
note expanded from "PAGEDU64 (not MDMP)" to the three signatures
DumpAnalyzer actually parses (PAGEDU64/PAGEDUMP, MDMP, PAGE).
